The paper discusses human navigation on the Web, which is a topic related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of Markov chain models for understanding navigation patterns suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and information science (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the structure of navigation patterns, which could fall under computational linguistics (cs.CL) or cybernetics (cs.CY).
